I thought it was a great recipe, especially for someone who's never made this before. I applied some of the previous suggestions - mushrooms, peppers, italian seasoning. My store had no scallops, so I opted for crab meat and the required shrimp. I changed up the sauce a bit. It calls for dry white wine, but I know Rose wine pairs well with seafood, so I used 1/4 cup with the whipping cream. Great to have a chilled glass with dinner too as it picks up the flavour already in the meal. The only thing I would change the next time I make it, is the amount of whipping cream. To me it's so heavy that it almost drowned out the flavour of everything else. I had to use a LOT of seasoning and way more salt than I normally do. Probably substitte 1/2 with a bit of lite cream. I'm not a super chef, but does anyone know if half-and-half or table cream would be better?

