Rating: 3
I hope my fellow searchers will appreciate my wholesale changes to this (fine) recipe, and find them helpful. I wanted seafood pasta with a cajun twist, and wanted to use up ingredients on hand. I wanted to save time by finding a recipe (this one) that gave me a solid-to-liquid ratio and had a roux-type component. Substitutions: 1 t. cajun spice for the coriander (plus some, & some cayenne); some half & half instead of all cream; crab instead of scallops. Additions: the greens of some scallions, some baby portabello mushrooms, about 2 oz. andouille sausage (diced) and 1/2 a yellow (or red) pepper. I needed more half & half, as the crab thickened it (plus the extra solids). VERY tasty -- hubby loved it and will make again this weekend for my Lousiana friends!

